 citizen who lived in Rome, Paris, Provence, Venice, Miami, and Manhattan across his career."},{"number":3,"category":"civic","header":"Forty years preserving great-aunt Anne Morgan's WWI legacy","body":"Miles spent four decades championing the legacy of his great-aunt Anne Morgan, daughter of John Pierpont Morgan and organizer of WWI relief from the Château de Blérancourt in Picardy. He toured an 18-city exhibition on American women rebuilding France, secured a 2019 PBS broadcast of the film Anne Morgan's War, and served on the scientific committee when the Blérancourt museum was rebuilt in 2016. France honored him with the Légion d'Honneur and the rank of Officier in the Ordre des Arts et Lettres."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"HD1174","link_text":"Anne Tracy Morgan","display_label":"Great-aunt; Miles preserved her WWI legacy across forty years."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Miles Morgan","first_name":"Miles","last_name":"Morgan","married_names":[],"gender":"male"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[{"war":"Korean War","war_id":"WAR014","rank_year_start":1951,"rank_year_end":1953,"unit":"United States Army","notes":"U.S. Army 1951-1953 — Korean War era service. Specific unit, rank, and theater of service undocumented. Per existing research_notes on this entry. Son of Henry Sturgis Morgan (HD1175) of the J.P. Morgan banking dynasty."}],"former_ids":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM025","plot_notes":"Cedar Hill Cemetery, Hartford CT — Morgan family plot. Same cemetery as his father Henry Sturgis Morgan (HD1175, 1900-1982 Morgan Stanley co-founder), grandfather John Pierpont Morgan II (HD1172, 1867-1943), and great-grandfather John Pierpont Morgan (HD1170, 1837-1913 of J.P. Morgan & Co.)."},"education":[],"career":[],"slug":"miles-morgan-1928"},"HD3130":{"id":"HD3130","is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_